    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Board
    The Board class represents the game board for the Snake game.
    Candy
    The Candy record represents a piece of candy on the board.
    GameController
    This class controls the overall flow of the Snake game, acting as the primary controller in the Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture.
    GameLogicController
    This class handles the core game logic of the Snake game, including board management, snake movement, collision detection, and game state updates.
    GameLogicController.GameState
    Enum representing the possible game states.
    GameLogicController.PointChecker
    A functional interface used to check if a point (segment) lies within a specified area.
    GamePanel
    The GamePanel class represents the graphical user interface (GUI) panel where the Snake game is displayed.
    GameResult<T>
    The GameResult class represents the result of a game.
    InvalidName
    A custom exception class that is thrown when a player's name is invalid.
    NeedsOptimization
    The NeedsOptimization annotation is used to mark methods that require optimization.
    Player
    The Player class represents a player in the Snake game.
    Snake
    The Snake class represents the snake in the Snake game.
    StartPanel
    The StartPanel class represents the starting screen of the game where the user can input their name, choose a color, and start the game.
    TerminalTester
    A simple class for displaying output in the console.
